==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Boor
<hw>Boor</hw> <pr>(b⟦oomac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>boer</ets> farmer, boor; akin to AS. <ets>geb⟦umac⟧r</ets>
countryman, G. <ets>bauer</ets>; fr. the root of AS.
<ets>b⟦umac⟧an</ets> to inhabit, and akin to E. <ets>bower</ets>,
<ets>be</ets>. Cf. <er>Neighbor</er>, <er>Boer</er>, and <er>Big</er> to
build.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A husbandman; a peasant; a rustic; esp. a
clownish or unrefined countryman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A Dutch, German, or Russian peasant; esp. a Dutch
colonist in South Africa, Guiana, etc.: a boer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A rude ill-bred person; one who is clownish in
manners.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boone</ent>⟦br⟧
